        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 1 at 6:55PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 654 PM EDT, a line of strong thunderstorms was along a line
extending from Carrollton to Plant Wansley to near Franklin, and
moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, frequent cloud to ground lightning and
heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects. Heavy rain may cause temporary
street flooding especially in poor drainage areas.

Locations impacted include...
Carrollton, Franklin, Whitesburg, Centralhatchee, Roopville, Corinth,
Plant Yates, Byers Crossroads, Hannah, Arnco-Sargent, Powers
Crossroads, Seaton Lake, Fairplay, Handy, Clem, Lowell, and Plant
Wansley.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning. Motorists
should slow down and be prepared for possible loss of control due to
hydroplaning.</instruction>
